  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Intensive care unit (ICU) admission is associated with muscle weakness and ICU survivors
      report persevering limitation of physical capacity for years after discharge. Limited
      information is available about the underlying biomechanical properties responsible for this
      muscle function impairment.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
